## Current Project State (snapshot)

Working prototype. Multi-crate Cargo workspace under `crates/`. SQLite + FTS5 storage,
sqlite-vec ANN search, catalog-driven provider selection, unified inference queue
(`InferenceQueue`), hybrid search pipeline, bulk graph access (`get_all_edges`,
`get_nodes_paginated`). Interactive RAG chat REPL (`cli_chat`). No active bugs.

The core library has been fully refactored (hardware abstraction layer removed):
- `hardware/` directory deleted ‚Äî `NpuDevice`, `GpuDevice`, `CpuDevice`, `DeviceWorker`
  trait, and `HardwareBackend` enum no longer exist.
- `lemonade/device_factory.rs`, `lemonade/model_limits.rs`, `lemonade/registry.rs`,
  `lemonade/stack.rs` deleted. `LemonadeModelRegistry`, `ModelRole`, `LemonadeStack`,
  `EmbeddingManager`, and `TranscriptionManager` no longer exist.
- Replaced by: `lemonade/catalog.rs` (`LemonadeServerCatalog`), `lemonade/selector.rs`
  (`ModelSelector`, `SelectedModel`, `QualityTier`), `lemonade/duplicate_guard.rs`
  (`DuplicateGuard`), `lemonade/provider_factory.rs` (`ProviderFactory`, `Capability`,
  `BuiltProvider`).
- `ai/embeddings.rs` and `ai/transcription.rs` are trait-only files; implementations
  live in `lemonade/embedding.rs` and `lemonade/transcription.rs`.
- `InferenceQueueBuilder` now wires providers via `.with_provider(BuiltProvider)` /
  `.with_providers(Vec<BuiltProvider>)`. `ProviderFactory::build()` constructs them.
- `AppConfig` now includes `[chat]` section with per-device model overrides
  (`[chat.gpu]`, `[chat.npu]`). `ModelConfig.load_params` replaces the old
  `context_limits: HashMap`.

