## Always Read First

> **`.rulesdir/project-structure.mdc`**

Read for every task. Module map, current architecture, migration status, key
integration points, hardware capability table.

---

## Task-Based Routing

### Building, running, or setting up the environment
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/environment-config.mdc`**
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/development-workflow.mdc`**

`env.sh` is **optional** ‚Äî no longer required for compilation. `cargo build` and
`cargo test` work with no env vars. See these files for Lemonade Server setup and
the `LEMONADE_URL` auto-discovery order.

---

### Writing or modifying Rust source (`src/**/*.rs`, `examples/*.rs`)
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`**

Error handling (`anyhow`), `EmbeddingProvider` trait (do NOT bypass it),
`TranscriptionProvider` trait, `InferenceQueue` usage, `ObjectBuilder`, async
anti-patterns, storage patterns, tracing instrumentation.

---

### Adding or wiring a new AI capability (embedding, reranking, TTS, STT, LLM)
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`** (EmbeddingProvider / trait sections)
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/development-workflow.mdc`** (provider addition workflow)

New providers implement the relevant trait (`EmbeddingProvider` or
`TranscriptionProvider`). For queue-dispatched work, build via `ProviderFactory` and
register with `InferenceQueueBuilder::with_provider`. Do NOT call provider HTTP
clients directly from business logic. Do NOT use `Mutex<T>` in async paths.
There is no `DeviceWorker` trait ‚Äî that abstraction was removed in the hardware
refactor.

---

### Writing, running, or debugging tests
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/testing-debugging.mdc`**
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`** (testing patterns section)

Re-read anti-pattern ¬ß1 above before writing any test. Every test gets its own
`TempDir`. Mock providers for unit tests; `lemonade_url().await` skip-guard for
integration tests.

---

### Schema files (`defaults/schemas/*.schema.json`)
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/schema-system.mdc`**
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/json-data-formats.mdc`**

`add_` prefix convention, `SchemaIngestion` stripping, property types, the 13
built-in TTRPG types.

---

### Data files (`defaults/data/*.json`) or the import pipeline
‚Üí **`.rulesdir/json-data-formats.mdc`**

JSONL node/edge format, two-pass import, deduplication, edge resolution.

---


